Project Objective

The objective of this project was to develop an interactive Power BI dashboard for JCars Logistics Company by importing raw sales data into an Aiven PostgreSQL database, connecting the database to Power BI, cleaning and transforming the data, creating business measures using DAX, and developing interactive visualizations to support management decision-making.

Importing Data into Aiven PostgreSQL

The JCars Logistics dataset was imported into an Aiven PostgreSQL cloud database using SQL tools.

The process involved:

Creating a PostgreSQL service in Aiven.
Creating a new database.
Importing the cleaned JCars Logistics dataset into the database.
Verifying that all records were successfully loaded.
Confirming that all tables and columns matched the source dataset.
Connecting Power BI to Aiven PostgreSQL

Power BI was connected to the cloud database using the PostgreSQL connector.

The connection process included:

Selecting PostgreSQL Database as the data source.
Entering the Aiven hostname, port number, database name, username, and password.
Installing and configuring the SSL certificate provided by Aiven.
Authenticating the connection.
Loading the tables into Power BI.
Data Cleaning and Preparation

The following data preparation tasks were completed:

Removed duplicate records.
Corrected data types.
Standardized date fields.
Handled missing values.
Removed invalid records.
Created the Delivery Time field.
Verified relationships and data consistency.
Prepared the dataset for reporting.
